# Fantasy Forge Engine - Player Guide

Welcome, adventurer! This guide will teach you everything you need to survive.

---

## Controls

| Key | Action |
|-----|--------|
| `↑` `↓` `←` `→` | Move (or `h` `j` `k` `l` vim-style) |
| `Enter` / `Space` | Interact / Confirm |
| `Esc` | Cancel / Back |
| `i` | Open Inventory |
| `e` | Open Equipment |
| `s` | Status / Stats |
| `q` | Quit Game |

### In Menus

| Key | Action |
|-----|--------|
| `↑` `↓` | Navigate options |
| `Enter` | Select |
| `Esc` | Close menu |
| `Tab` | Switch tabs (in shops) |

### In Combat

| Key | Action |
|-----|--------|
| `↑` `↓` | Select action |
| `Enter` | Confirm action |
| `←` `→` | Select target (if multiple) |

---

## Getting Started

1. **Create your character** — Pick a name and class
2. **Explore the town** — Talk to NPCs, find shops
3. **Buy equipment** — Weapon and armor help a lot
4. **Save at the inn** — This is your respawn point!
5. **Venture out** — Fight monsters, gain XP, level up
6. **Return to heal** — Don't push too far without healing

**Golden rule:** Save early, save often. Death hurts.

---

## Character Classes

| Class | HP | MP | Strengths | Weaknesses |
|-------|----|----|-----------|------------|
| **Warrior** | ★★★ | ★ | High damage, tanky | No magic |
| **Mage** | ★ | ★★★ | Powerful spells, AoE | Fragile, needs MP |
| **Rogue** | ★★ | ★★ | Fast, critical hits, steal | Lower defense |
| **Cleric** | ★★ | ★★★ | Healing, buffs, undead killer | Weak damage |
| **Ranger** | ★★ | ★★ | Balanced, multi-shot | Master of none |

### Stat Breakdown

| Stat | What It Does |
|------|--------------|
| **STR** | Physical damage |
| **AGI** | Speed, dodge chance, escape success |
| **VIT** | HP growth, defense |
| **INT** | Magic damage, MP growth |
| **LUK** | Critical hits, item drops |

### Derived Stats

| Stat | Formula |
|------|---------|
| **Attack** | STR + Weapon |
| **Defense** | VIT/2 + Armor |
| **Speed** | AGI (determines turn order) |
| **Magic Atk** | INT |
| **Magic Def** | INT/2 + VIT/4 |

---

## Combat

Combat is turn-based. You and enemies take turns based on **Speed**.

### Your Options

| Action | Effect |
|--------|--------|
| **Attack** | Basic physical attack |
| **Skill** | Use a learned ability (costs MP) |
| **Defend** | Reduce damage taken this turn, +4 AC |
| **Item** | Use a potion or consumable |
| **Flee** | Attempt to escape (not always possible) |

### How Attacks Work

```
Hit Check:    Roll d20 + your Attack vs enemy AC
Damage:       Weapon dice + STR bonus
Critical:     Natural 20 = double damage!
```

### Combat Tips

- **Defend** when low HP and waiting for heals
- **Flee** works better with high AGI (base 30% + AGI×2, max 90%)
- Some zones prevent escape (boss fights, certain dungeons)
- Dying respawns you at the last inn with **1 HP** and **half your gold**

---

## The World

### Map Tiles

| Symbol | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| `@` | You |
| `.` | Floor (walkable) |
| `#` | Wall (blocked) |
| `+` | Door (walk into to open) |
| `X` | Locked door (need key) |
| `<` | Stairs up |
| `>` | Stairs down |
| `~` | Water (blocked) |
| `^` | Trap (damages you) |
| `*` | Chest (walk into to open) |
| `$` | Gold pile |
| `!` | Item pickup |
| `S` | Shop |
| `I` | Inn |
| `M` | Monster (visible spawn) |
| `N` | NPC |

### Map Types

| Type | Encounters? | Description |
|------|-------------|-------------|
| **Town** | No | Safe zone, shops, inns, NPCs |
| **Overworld** | Yes | Open travel between areas |
| **Dungeon** | Yes | Monster-filled, loot-rich |
| **Building** | No | Indoor areas, usually safe |

---

## Shops

Walk onto an `S` tile and press Enter to open the shop.

### Buying

- Items cost gold (price shown)
- Red price = you can't afford it
- Some items have limited stock
- Stock may refill over time (game days)

### Selling

- Press Tab to switch to Sell mode
- You get ~40-50% of item value
- Sell junk, keep good equipment

### Shop Types

| Type | What They Sell |
|------|----------------|
| **General** | Potions, food, basic supplies |
| **Weapon** | Swords, axes, staves, daggers |
| **Armor** | Body armor, shields, helmets |
| **Magic** | Scrolls, wands, mage gear |

---

## Inns

Walk onto an `I` tile and press Enter.

### What Inns Do

- **Rest** — Fully restore HP and MP (costs gold)
- **Save** — Write your progress to a save slot
- **Set Checkpoint** — If you die, you respawn here

### Pro Tips

- Always save before entering a new dungeon
- Resting advances the game day (shops may restock)
- Some inns are free (castle guest rooms, etc.)
- You have **3 save slots** — use them!

---

## Inventory & Equipment

### Inventory (press `i`)

- Holds up to **20 item stacks**
- Stackable items (potions, food) stack to 99
- Use items directly from inventory

### Equipment (press `e`)

| Slot | What Goes There |
|------|-----------------|
| **Weapon** | Swords, axes, staves, daggers |
| **Armor** | Body protection |
| **Shield** | Off-hand defense |
| **Helmet** | Head protection |
| **Ring** | Stat bonuses |
| **Amulet** | Stat bonuses |

### Item Rarity

| Color | Rarity | Quality |
|-------|--------|---------|
| White | Common | Basic |
| Green | Uncommon | Decent |
| Blue | Rare | Good |
| Purple | Epic | Great |
| Orange | Legendary | Best |

---

## Leveling Up

Defeat monsters to earn **XP**. When you earn enough, you level up!

### What You Get

- Increased max HP and MP
- Stat boosts (varies by class)
- New skills at certain levels
- Full HP/MP restore

### XP Tips

- Stronger monsters give more XP
- Don't grind forever in starting areas
- Push into harder zones as you level

---

## Skills

Skills are special abilities learned as you level.

### Skill Types

| Type | Description |
|------|-------------|
| **Attack** | Deal damage (often with bonus effects) |
| **Heal** | Restore HP to self or allies |
| **Buff** | Increase stats temporarily |
| **Debuff** | Weaken enemies |
| **Utility** | Steal, scan, etc. |

### MP Management

- Skills cost MP
- Blue potions restore MP
- Some inns restore MP for free
- Mages burn through MP fast—bring potions!

---

## Death

When your HP hits 0:

1. **Death screen** appears
2. Choose: **Load Save**, **Respawn at Inn**, or **Quit**

### Respawn Penalty

- Teleport to last inn you saved at
- HP set to **1** (heal up!)
- Lose **half your gold**

**Tip:** Bank your gold by buying items before dangerous dungeons.

